The paper proposes a new optimization algorithm for deep neural networks, which is a fundamental topic in machine learning and falls under the category of "Learning" (cs.LG). The proposed algorithm is evaluated on various computer vision tasks such as ImageNet and CIFAR-10/100, which suggests that the paper could also be categorized under "Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition" (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of the algorithm on neural machine translation and Penn Treebank, indicating that it could also be classified under "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI) and "Computation and Language" (cs.CL). Finally, the paper proposes a new approach that is orthogonal to existing optimization algorithms, which could be of interest to researchers in the field of "Neural and Evolutionary Computing" (cs.NE).
